  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tbsp olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add minced garlic and grated ginger. Cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add Chinese broccoli to the saucepan and cook for 2 minutes. Add soy sauce and stir to coat.",
    "Add honey, sesame oil, salt, and black pepper to the saucepan. Stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer for 3-5 minutes, or until the broccoli is tender.",
    "Stir in chopped fresh parsley and crushed red pepper flakes. Cook for an additional minute.",
    "Serve the broccoli hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
